OL,3,CWhy can the suspect in the Southport
OL,4,Cattack now be named?
OL,6,FThe identity of defendants and
OL,7,Fwitnesses under the age of 18 who are
OL,8,Fsubject to criminal proceedings in
OL,9,Fyouth courts is protected by automatic
OL,10,Freporting restrictions under Section
OL,11,F49 of the Children and Young Persons
OL,12,FAct 1933.
OL,14,FIf a child is charged with an offence
OL,15,Fand is facing criminal proceedings in
OL,16,Fadult courts ` magistrates' and crown
OL,17,Fcourts ` then magistrates and judges
OL,18,Fhave legal powers to grant anonymity
OL,19,Fto a child defendant, witness or
OL,20,Fvictim under Section 45 of the Youth
OL,21,FJustice and Criminal Evidence Act 1999.
