OL,3,CWhy can the suspect in the Southport
OL,4,Cattack now be named?
OL,6,FBoth of these laws ban the press from
OL,7,Fpublishing a child defendant's name or
OL,8,Fany detail which could lead to them
OL,9,Fbeing identified while the reporting
OL,10,Frestrictions remain in place.
OL,12,FThis is why media reports sometimes
OL,13,Fsay they cannot identify a child
OL,14,Finvolved in a criminal court case for
OL,15,Flegal reasons.
OL,17,FThe automatic restrictions technically
OL,18,Fbegin once court proceedings are
OL,19,Factive ` when a suspect has been
OL,20,Fcharged and is appearing in court for
OL,21,Fthe first time.
