OL,3,CWhy can the suspect in the Southport
OL,4,Cattack now be named?
OL,6,FPress regulator IPSO advises editors
OL,7,Fto "generally avoid naming children
OL,8,Funder the age of 18 after arrest for a
OL,9,Fcriminal offence but before they
OL,10,Fappear in a youth court unless they
OL,11,Fcan show that the individual's name is
OL,12,Falready in the public domain, or that
OL,13,Fthe individual (or, if they are under
OL,14,F16, a custodial parent or similarly
OL,15,Fresponsible adult) has given their
OL,16,Fconsent", adding: "This does not
OL,17,Frestrict the right to name juveniles
OL,18,Fwho appear in a crown court, or whose
OL,19,Fanonymity is lifted."
