OL,3,CWhy can the suspect in the Southport
OL,4,Cattack now be named?
OL,6,FIf a child is convicted of a crime,
OL,7,Fhaving either pleaded guilty or been
OL,8,Ffound guilty after a trial, then
OL,9,Fmagistrates and judges have powers to
OL,10,Flift reporting restrictions so the
OL,11,Fdefendant can be identified in some
OL,12,Fcircumstances, including if this is
OL,13,Fconsidered in the public interest.
OL,15,FMedia may try to challenge the
OL,16,Fanonymity order if identifying the
OL,17,Fchild could help to maintain public
OL,18,Fconfidence in the justice system, or
OL,19,Fdeter others from offending, by
OL,20,Fallowing full details of the case to
OL,21,Fbe reported.
